The Jia Wei Chinese Restaurant, found within the Grand Mercure Singapore Roxy, has introduced a new menu to coincide with the arrival of their new head chef, Victor. The dishes are meant to complement the restaurant&rsquo;s modern Eastern aesthetic and embody the Chinese principle of &ldquo;家味,&rdquo; signifying &ldquo;flavors of home.&rdquo;
The menu features popular Eastern dishes like Chef&rsquo;s superior fish maw served with seafood soup, and fresh prawns accompanied by two special sauces.
